info.headline: High Wind Warning issued October 11 at 2:35AM MDT until October 11 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM MDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts around 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County including Interstate 25 between Wheatland and Chugwater, North Snowy Range Foothills including Interstate 80 between Laramie and Rawlins. * WHEN...Until 3PM MDT this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Mainly to to transportation. Strong cross winds could be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
